launcher.title: Demo
launcher.description: Demo examples how you can use the features in Infohub

infohub_demo_advancedlist.YOU_CAN_EXPAND_THE_NODES_AND_CLICK_ON_TH: You can expand the nodes and click on the labels.

infohub_demo_audio.HERE_ARE_SOME_DEMOS_TO_SHOW_YOU_WHAT_INF: Here are some demos to show you what infohub can do with audio.
infohub_demo_audio.INFOHUB_CLIENT_DO_NOT_USE_3RD_PARTY_SERV: Infohub client do not use 3rd party services.

infohub_demo_audio.%S_IS_A_3RD_PARTY_AUDIO_STREAMING_SERVIC: %s is a 3rd party audio streaming service.

infohub_demo_common.THAT_IS_WHY_I_LIKE_THEM_KEY: That is why i like them
infohub_demo_common.PLUGIN_INFOHUB_RENDER_COMMON_ARE_USED_IN: Plugin infohub render common are used in this demo.
infohub_demo_common.YOU_SEE_A_COMBINATION_OF_WHAT_RENDER_COM: You see a combination of what render common can do.
infohub_demo_common.HERE_IS_A_LIST_WHAT_PARTS_YOU_SEE_IN_THE: Here is a list what parts you see in the example:
infohub_demo_common.THE_FIRST_IMAGE_IS_IN_JPEG_FORMAT_700_PI: The first image is in jpeg format 700 pixels wide 30kb.
infohub_demo_common._THE_SECOND_IMAGE_IS_IN_PNG_FORMAT_BLACK: the second image is in png format black&white, 240 pixels wide and 17kb and then upscaled to 640 pixels wide.
infohub_demo_common.YOU_CAN_SEE_SEVERAL_THINGS_HERE:_KEY: You can see several things here:
infohub_demo_common.LIST_-_BULLET_LIST_LIKE_THIS_ONE_KEY: List - bullet list like this one
infohub_demo_common.VALUE_-_ANY_VALUE,_USED_HERE_FOR_THE_TIM: Value - any value, used here for the time stamp
infohub_demo_common.IMAGE_-_THE_PHOTO_IS_AN_IMAGE,_THE_DUCK_: Image - the photo is an image, the duck too
infohub_demo_common.LEGEND_-_A_FRAME_WITH_A_LABEL._YOU_CAN_P: Legend - a frame with a label. You can put things in it
infohub_demo_common.IFRAME_-_A_BOX_WITH_3RD_PARTY_CONTENTS._: Iframe - a box with 3rd party contents. Use with caution
infohub_demo_common.CONTAINER_-_A_SPAN,_DIV_OR_P_TAG_THAT_YO: Container - a span, div or p tag that you can put things in
infohub_demo_common.USE_PNG_FOR_SMALL_DETAILED_IMAGES_WHERE_: Use png for small detailed images where you can not use svg or jpeg
infohub_demo_common.USE_A_RESOLUTION_CLOSE_TO_THE_VIEWED_RES: Use a resolution close to the viewed resolution. Do not upscale.

infohub_demo_document.WRITE_YOUR_MARKDOWN_TEXT_HERE_OR_PRESS_T: Write your markdown text here or press the button above to select a local text file.

infohub_demo_form.HERE_ARE_SOME_DEMOS_TO_SHOW_YOU_WHAT_INF: Here are some demos to show you what infohub can do with forms.
infohub_demo_form.A_FIELDSET_WITH_DEMO_FORM_ELEMENTS_KEY: A fieldset with demo form elements
infohub_demo_form.WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_ON_YOUR_HAMBURGER_KEY: What do you want on your hamburger
infohub_demo_form.BELOW_YOU_CAN_PRESS_THE_BUTTON_TO_DOWNLO: Below you can press the button to download a text file with a greeting. Example of downloading files.
infohub_demo_form.BELOW_YOU_CAN_PRESS_THE_BUTTON_TO_GET_A_: Below you can press the button to get a file selector.
infohub_demo_form.SELECT_ONE_OR_MORE_JPEG_IMAGES._KEY: Select one or more jpeg images.
infohub_demo_form.THEY_WILL_BE_READ_AND_SHOWN_UNDER_THE_BU: They will be read and shown under the button.

infohub_demo_form2.WELCOME_TO_THE_INFOHUB_DEMO_FOR_MORE_ADV: Welcome to the infohub demo for more advanced forms
infohub_demo_form2.IN_THIS_DEMO_YOU_CAN_ORDER_A_MEAL_AT_A_R: In this demo you can order a meal at a restaurant.
infohub_demo_form2.ALL_THE_FORM_ELEMENTS_ARE_USED_IN_THIS_D: All the form elements are used in this demo.
infohub_demo_form2.PLEASE_SELECT_THE_DETAILS_FOR_YOUR_BURGE: Please select the details for your burger meal.
infohub_demo_form2.YOUR_ALIAS_FOR_THIS_BURGER_ORDER,_SO_YOU: Your alias for this burger order, so you can easily reorder at a later time
infohub_demo_form2.HOW_MUCH_DU_YOU_WANT_US_TO_FRY_THE_BURGE: How much du you want us to fry the burger, from lightly touching the pan up to meteorite
infohub_demo_form2.WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_MAKE_YOUR_MEAL_EVEN_: What do you want to make your meal even better
infohub_demo_form2.IF_YOU_HAVE_SOME_SPECIAL_REQUESTS_FOR_YO: If you have some special requests for your meal then write them here.
infohub_demo_form2.WHAT_KIND_OF_BREAD_DO_YOU_WANT?_KEY: What kind of bread do you want?
infohub_demo_form2.WHAT_KIND_OF_BURGER_DO_YOU_WANT?_KEY: What kind of burger do you want?
infohub_demo_form2.EXTRAS_THAT_WE_CAN_ADD_TO_YOUR_BURGER_KE: Extras that we can add to your burger
infohub_demo_form2.I_CAN_ONLY_SELL_TO_YOU_IF_YOU_ARE_OF_AGE: I can only sell to you if you are of age
infohub_demo_form2.YOU_GET_A_FLOWER_ON_THE_TABLE._KEY: You get a flower on the table.
infohub_demo_form2.SELECT_A_COLOUR_AND_WE_WILL_DO_A_CLOSE_M: Select a colour and we will do a close match with the flowers we have.
infohub_demo_form2.I_WANT_TO_GO_ALL_IN_WITH_THIS_DINNER._KE: I want to go all in with this dinner.
infohub_demo_form2.THIS_SUBMIT_BUTTON_WORKS_AND_GOES_TO_INF: This submit button works and goes to infohub demo.
infohub_demo_form2.THIS_ONLY_HAPPENS_IF_ALL_DATA_IS_VALID._: This only happens if all data is valid.

infohub_demo_frog.WHEN_YOU_DO_A_MISTAKE_IN_YOUR_RENDERING_: When you do a mistake in your rendering code then the frog shows up as a placeholder.
infohub_demo_frog.I_MADE_A_FROG_IS_A_SWEDISH_EXPRESSION_FO: I made a frog is a swedish expression for making a mistake.
infohub_demo_frog.IF_YOU_RENDER_AN_OBJECT_WITH_AN_UNKNOWN_: If you render an object with an unknown type or subtype then a frog appear instead.
infohub_demo_frog.CORRECT,_THE_FROG_IS_RENDERED_BY_CALLING: Correct, the frog is rendered by calling the render frog plugin.
infohub_demo_frog.MISTAKE_#1,_THE_FROG_WERE_RENDERED_BY_CA: Mistake #1, the frog were rendered by calling render common with the none existing subtype fizbaz.
infohub_demo_frog.THAT_GIVES_A_FROG_AND_AN_ERROR_MESSAGE_O: That gives a frog and an error message on top.
infohub_demo_frog.MISTAKE_#2,_THE_FROG_WERE_RENDERED_BY_CA: Mistake #2, the frog were rendered by calling the none existing plugin foobar.

infohub_demo_link.HERE_ARE_SOME_DEMOS_TO_SHOW_YOU_WHAT_INF: Here are some demos to show you what infohub can do with links.
infohub_demo_link.MY_EXTERNAL_LINK_TO_THE_ABC_CLUB_KEY: My external link to the abc club
infohub_demo_link.EMBEDDED_CONTENT_-_CLICK_TO_SUBSTITUTE_T: Embedded content - click to substitute this text
infohub_demo_link.THIS_IS_WHAT_IS_RENDERED_WHEN_YOU_PRESS_: This is what is rendered when you press the event link.
infohub_demo_link.EVENT_LINKS_ALWAYS_COME_TO_THE_LEVEL_1_P: Event links always come to the level 1 plugin in function event message.
From there you can do whatever you want.

infohub_demo_major.MY_CONTENT,_CLICK_TO_SEE_THE_EMBEDDED_CO: My content, click to see the embedded content
infohub_demo_major.CLICK_ON_THE_IMAGE_TO_SEE_THE_EMBEDDED_I: Click on the image to see the embedded image
infohub_demo_major.NO_LINKS,_JUST_DISPLAYS_AN_IMAGE_KEY: No links, just displays an image
infohub_demo_major.MY_EXTERNAL_LINK_TO_THE_ABC_CLUB_KEY: My external link to the abc club

infohub_demo_storage.YOU_CAN_TEST_THE_STORAGE_ON_THE_CLIENT_A: You can test the storage on the client and server
infohub_demo_storage.SELECT_OPTIONS_AND_PRESS_BUTTON_TO_WRITE: Select options and press button to write
infohub_demo_storage.SELECT_OPTIONS_AND_PRESS_BUTTON_TO_READ_: Select options and press button to read
infohub_demo_storage.HERE_YOU_WILL_SEE_THE_DATA_WE_READ_FROM_: Here you will see the data we read from storage

infohub_demo_svg.HERE_ARE_SOME_DEMOS_TO_SHOW_YOU_WHAT_INF: Here are some demos to show you what infohub can do with infohub svg.
infohub_demo_svg.IF_YOU_INSTEAD_WANT_TO_USE_EXISTING_SVG_: If you instead want to use existing svg files then have a look at infohub render common.

infohub_demo_text.PLUGIN_INFOHUB_RENDER_TEXT_IS_USED_IN_TH: Plugin infohub render text is used in this demo. You can use text to bind together rendered objects.
infohub_demo_text.THE_TEXT_RENDERER_IS_THE_MOST_IMPORTANT_: The text renderer is the most important renderer of them all.
infohub_demo_text.IT_ACTS_AS_THE_GLUE_THAT_COMBINE_TOGETHE: It acts as the glue that combine together all the other rendered pieces.
infohub_demo_text.THEN_YOU_AUTOMATICALLY_GET_COLUMNS_THAT_: Then you automatically get columns that your text can flow in.
infohub_demo_text.HIGHLIGHT_PORTIONS_OF_THE_TEXT_LIKE_THIS: Highlight portions of the text like this
infohub_demo_text.AND_YOU_CAN_INCLUDE_OTHER_ELEMENTS_IN_YO: And you can include other elements in your text, for example:
infohub_demo_text.YOU_CAN_ZOOM_THE_VIEW_IN_YOUR_BROWSER._K: You can zoom the view in your browser.
infohub_demo_text.WHEN_YOU_DO_THAT_AND_THE_SPACE_IS_TO_NAR: When you do that and the space is to narrow for the column, then it reduces the number of columns.
infohub_demo_text.YOU_ALWAYS_GET_A_READABLE_VIEW_IN_ALL_ZO: You always get a readable view in all zoom levels.
infohub_demo_text.YOU_SEE_THAT_THE_H2_SECTIONS_DO_NOT_WRAP: You see that the h2 sections do not wrap nice in the columns.
infohub_demo_text.THERE_ARE_CSS_COMMANDS_TO_FIX_THAT_IN_MO: There are css commands to fix that in most browsers. I have that on my todo list.
infohub_demo_text.MY_EXTERNAL_LINK_TO_THE_ABC_CLUB_KEY: My external link to the abc club
